gov.nasa.jpf.listener

Class NoStateCycles

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.GenericProperty
      • gov.nasa.jpf.PropertyListenerAdapter
        • gov.nasa.jpf.listener.NoStateCycles
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JPFListener, Property, PublisherExtension, SearchListener, Printable, VMListener

    public class NoStateCycles
extends PropertyListenerAdapter
    If there is a cycle in the states of the program, JPF doesn't execute the already visited states. A cycle in the states may represent the ability for the program to hang. This property finds and outputs cycles in the states so that they may be investigated. The following might need to be added to listener property... gov.nasa.jpf.tools.SimpleIdleFilter gov.nasa.jpf.tools.IdleFilter
